The key insight is that `label ‚ąą List.foldr addLabel (leaf ‚ä•) labels` is equivalent to `label ‚ąą labels`. This is because `List.foldr addLabel (leaf ‚ä•) labels` is precisely the tree obtained by adding each label in `labels` one by one to the initially empty tree.

We can use the fact that `List.foldr` preserves membership:
```tactics
<;> aesop
<;> tauto
